      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T12:18:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the detailed feedback.\nI\u0027ve updated target-fail-monitoring.md in [88393] with the JSON format, design details, and testing steps. The full JSON example is also in the commit message here and [87257].\n\nFully agree that BMC quiesce should be avoided for services that recover fine — the two keys serve different severity levels: \"services\" only quiesces after all restart retries are exhausted, while \"immediate_quiesce_services\" fires on the first failure for services where even a brief crash causes irreparable damage. \n\nThe feature is configured per platform based on its own needs — [87257] set it up for yosemite4 as an example, though whether it stays long-term is still up to the platform maintainers.\n\n[88393]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/88393\n[87257]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/87257\n[88357]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/88357",
